5:
Interesting... There's nothing to worry
about. It's a type of common cold
that also affects the beastfolk from
our world.
8:
Make sure you take this medicine.
Can you do that for me?
19:
Most people lighten up when I
meow. Are my fluffy ears not
effective against other beastfolk?
23:
Maybe they're just used to seeing
ears like that?
27:
Children have always been wary of
me. I suppose it's a good thing that I
didn't become a pediatrician.
30:
Most people who go through their
residency realize that ships are
easier to handle than children. Kids
are always so afraid of doctors.
33:
Huh, this has got me thinking...
Why'd you want to become a doctor
in the first place?
36:
It's been my dream since childhood,
thanks to a fateful encounter.
39:
You see, I was injured in a huge
accident aboard a ship when I was
young. Not an uncommon
occurrence for that world, but
nevertheless, we weren't prepared.
42:
A single doctor who happened upon
us managed to save many lives,
including mine.
47:
That must have been quite the
skilled doctor.
52:
I wouldn't say so. In fact, I'm a far
better doctor than they ever were.
54:
But what really inspired me wasn't
their medical ability—it was
watching them persevere in spite of
every obstacle.
57:
It left a lasting impression, to say the
least.
62:
Is that why you're going around
saving people? Because you want
to be like that doctor?
66:
Perhaps in the beginning, I was
driven by a desire to be like my hero.
69:
But now... Now I simply can't stand to
see others suffer when I know I can
help.
74:
We should attend to the rest of our
patients.
Could the next people in line—
78:
Is it true? Are there actually doctors
here?!
80:
Please, you have to help us! My
village... All the children, they're...
They're...
83:
Take a deep breath. You can tell me
what's happening on the way there.
87:
Everyone is afflicted by the same
symptoms: fever, vomiting, diarrhea,
and intense abdominal pain.
94:
Considering all of them fell ill at the
same time, it could be food
poisoning.
96:
B-but everyone had different meals,
and the adults are fine to boot...
99:
The issue here is not FOOD that
you've all ingested, but something
else.
102:
Alk. Light. I need you both to check
on the water supply. I have
equipment for measuring water
quality in my bag.
105:
First mate, I need you to go back to
the ship and bring more hands to
help. Have everyone carry as much
potable water as they can.
108:
We're combating dehydration, yes?
Understood. I'll check on other
villages on my way back.
111:
Hmm. This situation is starting to
make sense now.
115:
Liao, don't push yourself too hard,
okay?
118:
D-don't tell me you think the water
supply's contaminated... Are the
children going to be all right?
121:
I can't say for sure. The only thing we
can do now is alleviate the
symptoms and hope they have the
stamina to pull through.
124:
I shall do all I can to save every last
one of them, but I'll need your help.
128:
So don't give up. There's still plenty
of hope left.
134:
Thank goodness we managed to
get everyone back on their feet.
138:
Indeed.
You were spot on with your
assessment, Liao. The water supply
was truly contaminated...
141:
In these types of situations, the
children are always the first to show
symptoms.
144:
If we hadn't been here when we
were, the adults would have also
succumbed to the same symptoms,
leaving the children to slowly fade...
147:
Yikes... I don't even wanna picture
that...
151:
Are you sure you want to leave
without collecting any payment
though? We used quite a lot of our
supplies this time around.
156:
I'm sure. The Fellowship of Floof was
formed to provide treatment to all,
regardless of profit.
160:
Right, you're committed to your
ideal. But why are you so dedicated
to it?
165: Out of spite, I suppose you could say.
167:
During my residency, I met an
abundance of doctors who would
only treat the wealthy.
169:
They'd ignore mothers begging for
them to save their children, instead
choosing to curry favor with royalty
and government officials.
172:
I fell into despair, then rage. They
were a disgrace to the entire
practice of medicine. So I swore I'd
never become like them.
184:
I just wanted to say... It was really
cool how you saved us! Thank you!
187:
No thanks needed. I was just doing
my duty as a doctor... Meow.
192:
Are you a cat or something? Hey,
you should bark next!
199:
Out of spite, you said... It's almost
hard to believe, looking at you now.
202:
You're more like your hero than you
give yourself credit for, Liao.
206:
...Perhaps. I would be happy if that
were the case.
